Adult.description: Yellow-throated Vireos have a thicker hooked bill than Pine Warblers with distinct yellow spectacles and unstreaked flanks.

Adult female/immature male.description: Adult female/immature male Cape May Warblers have a thinner bill than Pine Warblers with more distinct streaking on the flanks.

Immature female.description: Immature Cape May Warblers have narrower wingbars than immature Pine Warblers with more distinct streaking on the flanks.

Nonbreeding female/immature male.description: Nonbreeding female/immature male Bay-breasted Warblers have a thinner bill, more obvious wingbars, and cleaner flanks (often with chestnut wash) than Pine Warblers.

Adult female (Northern).description: Yellow Warblers are brighter yellow overall than Pine Warblers and lack wingbars.

Immature (Northern).description: Immature Yellow Warblers are brighter yellow overall than Pine Warblers and lack wingbars.

Nonbreeding female/immature.description: Nonbreeding female/immature Blackpoll Warblers have a thinner bill, a longer eyeline, and more distinct wingbars than Pine Warblers.

Breeding female.description: Female Blackpoll Warblers have a thinner bill, a longer eyeline, and more distinct wingbars than Pine Warblers.
